                    <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Report by the Deputies</hi></p>
                    <p>The Ministers heard a Report on the work of the Deputies, submitted by the
                        outgoing Chairman.</p>
                    <p>The Council agreed to restrict the Hydro-electric Experts’ terms of reference
                        for the Mont Cenis district to a study of the guarantees to be given by
                        France to Italy in respect to water supplies.</p>
                    <p>The Experts’ terms of reference would not include a study of the
                        hydro-electric possibilities of the Mont Cenis plateau.</p>
                    <p>It was agreed that the Experts’ report would be submitted to the
                        Deputies.</p>
                    <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Austro-Italian Frontier</hi></p>
                    <p>After studying the Report drawn up by the Committee of Hydroelectric Experts
                        following the Austrian request for a minor rectification of the
                        Austro-Italian frontier in the north-eastern section of the Alto Adige, the
                        Council agreed that the request could not be regarded as constituting a
                        minor frontier rectification as stated in the Austrian Federal Government’s
                            <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of 30th May, 1946 (<gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M. (D) (46)</gloss> 92).<note n="95" xml:id="d196fn95"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_454">p.
                                454</ref>.</note></p>
                    <p>The Deputies would examine the question of the guarantees to be given to
                        Austria by Italy regarding the railway between Eastern and Northern Tyrol,
                        through Pusterthal.</p>
                    <pb facs="0620" n="598" xml:id="pg_598"/>
                    <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Franco-Italian Frontier</hi></p>
                    <p>The Council adopted the Report of the Committee of Hydroelectric Experts for
                        the Tenda and Briga district (<gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D)
                            (46)</gloss> 163).<note n="96" xml:id="d196fn96"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_483">p. 483</ref>.</note> After an
                        exchange of views the Council agreed to resume consideration of the Tenda
                        and Briga question at 5 p.m. on the same afternoon.</p>
